Msg.Desc: Failed to initialize source and destination databases.
Msg.ExtDesc:
Failure to initialize the source database is normally a result of the file not being readable in the current directory due to access permissions. If the file is accessible, it may be truncated or corrupt. Check access permissions and integrity of the file.
If the destination database could not be initialized, the most common cause is a lack of write permissions in the specified output directory. Check access permissions or select a different directory to write the database to.

Msg.Desc: %d %s during SPD2 / NA2 file import.
Msg.ExtDesc:
Warnings during import of an database record situations that should be examined before continuing work on the design layout. These items may require some action on your part to correct the data before proceeding.
Errors during import of the same database indicate that one or more design objects could not be created. As a result, the database is considered incomplete. In most situations, this will require hand editing of the SPD2 / NA2 file to correct.

Msg.Desc: Unable to create new database file %s for writing. Reason to follow...
Unable to open source SPD2 / NA2 file %s for reading.
%s import beginning.
%s import finished. Import %s.
%d %s processed successfully.
%d %s objects failed to be created.
Unable to add fillets to create teardrop from %s to %s. Line width of 0 specified.
Msg.ExtDesc:
The NA2 and SPD2 formats permit a teardrop line segment to have a zero line width specified at one end. As the Cadence IC Packaging tools create teardrops using fillet lines, it is not possible for the tool to reproduce these tapered segments.
To correct this issue, run the glossing or add fillet command on the pad at the specified location.

Msg.Desc: Unable to locate top level design section start. File cannot be imported.
Msg.ExtDesc:
The top-level token of a NA2 or SPD2 file is the design token. This contains all the information about the specific package database. If the design token is not present, there is no information in the file which can be imported.
This issue must be corrected by the tool which wrote the source file.

Msg.Desc: %s section missing from file.
Msg.ExtDesc:
This section is considered optional. Depending on the state of the design when it was written to disk, it is possible that no items of this type would yet exist.
You are being warned of this situation in case you feel this section should be present. If that is the case, re-export the database from the original design.

Msg.Desc: %s section missing from file. File cannot be imported without this section.
Msg.ExtDesc: This section is required in order to generate a Cadence MCM or SIP design from the source file. Without the information in this section, critical pieces of the design intent cannot be determined, and the integrity of the resulting database is in question. Re-export the SPD2 / NA2 file from the original design and import the new file.

Msg.Desc: Resolution section missing from file. Assuming units match current database settings.
Settings section missing from file. Information such as text block sizes may be inaccurate.
Source file version is %.1f, which is %s than the latest version supported (%.1f). The resulting database may be incomplete. Continue?
No Navigator_Data version information found. Compatibility assumed.
Msg.ExtDesc: The Navigator_Data token in an SPD2 / NA2 file specifies the format version with which this file was created. If the value for this field is not present, the tool will assume that it is ok for processing. However, you should carefully validate the resulting MCM / SIP database for integrity.

Msg.Desc: Unrecognized %s token %s seen on line %d.
Msg.ExtDesc: If the format version of this file is higher or lower than the supported versions, this token may not be understood. As a result, it will be ignored during processing.

Msg.Desc: %d additional closing parentheses were found during file parsing.
Msg.ExtDesc: The file may be incomplete or may have a quoted string missing either the start or end quote. If possible, regenerate the file from the original database. If you continue to receive this message with the new file, check for an improperly quoted string.

Msg.Desc: %d unmatched opening parentheses were found during file parsing.
Msg.ExtDesc: The file may be incomplete or may have a quoted string missing either the start or end quote. If possible, regenerate the file from the original database. If you continue to receive this message with the new file, check for an improperly quoted string.
